# High-Risk Domain Guardrails

These files require stricter caution because they affect security, data integrity, and tax correctness.

- Prefer minimal, reviewable changes over broad refactors.
- Add/update targeted tests for every behavioral change.
- Keep assumptions and warning text aligned with logic changes.
- Do not weaken app-lock gating, keychain handling, or delete/reset cascades.
- For sync semantics changes, preserve actionable-vs-informational conflict behavior.
- For tax logic changes, include threshold/boundary regression vectors.
